<h2>Overview</h2>
<p>The <code>autofocus</code> attribute automatically moves keyboard focus to an element when the page loads, or when a <a href="/docs/attributes/popover/"><code>popover</code></a> or <a href="/docs/elements/native/dialog/"><code>&lt;dialog&gt;</code></a> opens. It is a boolean attribute — its presence activates the behavior.</p>
<p><strong>Applies to:</strong> <a href="/docs/elements/native/input/"><code>&lt;input&gt;</code></a>, <a href="/docs/elements/native/select/"><code>&lt;select&gt;</code></a>, <a href="/docs/elements/native/textarea/"><code>&lt;textarea&gt;</code></a>, <a href="/docs/elements/native/button/"><code>&lt;button&gt;</code></a>, and any element with <a href="/docs/attributes/tabindex/"><code>tabindex</code></a></p>

<h2>Values</h2>

<table>
  <thead><tr><th>Value</th><th>Behavior</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td><code>autofocus</code> (present)</td><td>Element receives focus automatically when the page loads or its dialog/popover opens</td></tr>
    <tr><td>(absent)</td><td>No automatic focus. The default.</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

